$ Vim command: g
@ g

Here's a file:
code {
some text
# xyz: one
more text
foo bar baz
# xyz: second
final text
# xyz: final words
code }

I want to extract all text after `# xyz:`

I can do that with the global command:
code {
:let @a='' | g/^# xyz:/let @A=substitute(getline('.'), '^# xyz: \(.*\)', '\1' . nr2chr(10), '')
code }

sa:
  â†’ development/vim/commands[Ex commands]
